h3 Version 1

p.flow-text.
  This version was made using LWJGL, so I was limited in the kinds of visuals I could make and the speed of developing certain features, which is why I eventually switched to Unity. I still like the way it looks though. All of the graphics in the game are generated using OPENGL and GLSL shaders. I tried experimenting with a couple of different shaders to give the game a playful geometry wars feel. The shader that creates the auras around the planets and other objects in the game is my own creation, however the shader that generates the star background is from from Pablo Rom√°n Andrioli's Star Nest. I modified his code a bit in order to make the shader less graphically intensive so it can run smoothly on older machines. For this recording I had to turn the settings way down.

